inn1.comm: full on middle to start with, Cook defends solidly back to the bowler
gets one past the outside edge this time, hint of movement away from Cook who played inside the line
short of a length on the hip and it's turned around down to long leg...and we'll have buzzers as the throw hits the stumps and ricochets away for two more
full and outside off, left alone
short ball over middle and leg, Bell goes underneath it...made him hop about a bit
that's a good one to finish with, full at off stump and it holds its line past Bell's outside edge as he plays forward
good delivery outside off, left alone by Cook and it carries at chest height to Wade
full outside off, hint of shape back into Cook but it was wide enough to leave
more swing on this one but it started on leg stump and went past Cook's pads
that's lovely bowling, lures Cook into a drive against a pitched-up ball outside off and he was caught on the crease. Lucky not to get an edge
slips down the leg side again, the signs of the rustiness in Pattinson's game but he's getting some attractive movement
back outside off, too wide that way now and it's called again
makes him play, this ducked in from outside off and Cook defended to cover
poor delivery, short and down the leg side, Cook went for the pull but was some way from making contact
close! Gets one on target, full at off stump, 135kph, Cook prods at it without much footwork and it spoons towards mid-on before falling a few meters short
left alone outside off to end a 10-ball over
short of a length on leg stump, worked into midwicket
full at off stump, Cook drives it square but he's still pretty static in the crease
on leg stump, flicked down the long leg and this Coulter-Nile's throw is over Wade's head but at least doesn't cost any runs
good line just outside off, Bell leaves it on trusting the bounce as well as the line
superb fielding at cover, Smith flings himself low to his right to cut off Bell's sweetly-timed front-foot punch
back of a length on off stump, steered to cover
outside leg stump again, this time Cook catches up with it and gets another single to long leg
that's a better delivery, outside off to Bell with a hint of shape away and it's left alone
aggression from Bell, he advances down the pitch and aims to go over mid-off but instead the ball flies off a thick outside edge over the slips and fine of third man
full at off stump, confidently forward and pushes firmly to cover
a beauty! Goes across Cook and scoots past the outside edge as he shuffles across the crease
shapes back into Cook on a good length, defended square into the off side
goes up and over the off side to a length delivery, it easily clears the ring of fielders but then plugs in the outfield
angled into the pads, uses his wrists and tucks through midwicket
pushed into the pads again, 145kph, this time Cook doesn't make contact and the ball bobbles to the leg side
short and wide, Cook attempts to go up and over point but the ball bounces over his top edge
this time he makes contact, more width from Johnson and Cook flashes hard getting a healthy top edge over the slips...fully committed to the shot
follows up with a full delivery at the toes which is dug out towards mid-on
appeal for caught behind! Bell jabbed at a very full delivery and Wade went up for the catch, but the ball bounced out of the footmarks and Bell hit the ground in his shot
uses his feet again, gets a thick inside edge into his pads as he aims to drive through the off side
good delivery, targets Bell's feet and it swings...dug out to the off side
back of a length, Bell takes his bottom hand off the bat as he fends it to the leg side
he frees his arms square over the off side, this ball swung but it was too wide and meant Bell had room to go up and over point
over the top again, this time straight down the ground. It has more height than distance, plugging in the outfield about two thirds of the way to the rope. Good intent.
full at the stumps and worked to midwicket
short, down the leg side but Cook had moved across outside off as he went for the pull. Almost went over leg stump, but called wide
short of a length, Cook pulls again and it doesn't come out of the middle but splits the gap between midwicket and mid-on
crunched! This one had the power. Wasn't very short from Faulkner, but Cook latched on, fetching it from outside off and hammering through midwicket. More brute force than timing
driven firmly to mid-off
excellent stuff from Cook, he came across his stumps and picked this up from a length outside off and pulled it in the air behind square...one bounce over the boundary
pitches up outside, Cook quickly forward and drives sweetly to mid-off
back of a length on middle and off, defended to the covers
touch fuller, Bell drops it into the on side between midwicket and mid-on for a well-judged single
full outside off, 135kph, left alone
short ball, outside off stump, Cook goes for the pull but is beaten by the extra bounce and it's too high for the umpires
that's another strong shot by Cook, this time he cuts against some width from Coulter-Nile and goes over point
and again! There's a touch of anger and frustration in this batting from Cook, another poor delivery which was short and wide gets dispatched square of the wicket with the cut

three in a row...this time it's a lovely, flowing cover drive. This is a glimpse of the Cook the world game got used to see a while ago. Coulter-Nile tries to compensate by pitching up, but Cook takes a big stride forward and creams it through the off side
strangled appeal for lbw, nipped back into Bell but sounded like two noises...might have been two pads but it was high as well
now it's Bell on the pull short as this is dropped short, goes out to deep square
full outside off, gets forward and drives to mid-on
finds the outside edge, flies through the area that would be packed during a Test but today is worth a single to third man
this is lovely from Bell, comes at the bowler again then drives perfectly straight down the ground in the air...nearly plugs in the outfield again, but dribbles over the rope
same again! And this time it's timed much better, launched straight down the ground by Bell as this flying starts continues
full outside off, left alone
this one is cut off the front foot, hard into the ground and fielded by short point
another short ball, another boundary...Cook pulls fiercely just past a diving square where Christian wasn't miles away from pulling off a blinder
onto the front foot and drives to cover
gets forward and this takes an inside edge into the pads then rolls to mid-off
this is straight down the ground, not a common shot for Cook...it didn't come quite of the middle, the bat turned in his hand, but it was straight of mid-off
round the wicket, full and dug out back to the bowler
outside leg stump and turned through midwicket
touch short outside off, Cook back-cuts to short third man
drifts into the pads and tucked backward of square
drops short and it's pulled off the front foot through straight midwicket...long-on comes into action
onto the front foot, drives firmly into the ground and to cover
edged! But just wide of slip as he dived to his right. Full delivery, Bell comes into the drive and gets a thick edge just out of reach of Marsh at the lone slip
now this is fired down the leg side...another wide
on leg stump and that's a lovely piece of timing and placement by Bell as he flicks it in the air over midwicket
this one comes out of the screws as well, full outside off and Bell drives to cover
back of a length outside off, Bell watches it go through to the keeper
pushed into the pads and it's flicked through square leg
full outside off, driven wide of the diving cover but it wasn't really timed so mid-off can get around
defended to the off side

breakthrough! Another start not built on for Cook. Goes for the slog sweep, played over the top of the ball and it hits off stump. Was quite full for the shot. There may have been a little bottom edge. Maxwell does the trick again.
onto the front foot, blocked firmly to cover
played back to the bowler
angled outside leg stump, and Stokes connects with a strong sweep which beats deep square leg
touch quicker and flatter, played off the back foot to midwicket
the boundaries keep coming, Bell goes straight down the ground against a full delivery although it was in the air for quite a while but was too straight for mid-on...his bottom hand came into play
short of a length, opens the face to third man
full and wide, 140kph, Stokes chases it with a drive and gets beaten
gets square up this time as he aims to leg and a thick outside edge falls short of point
on leg stump and it's flicked wide of deep square-leg
oh, that's a stunner...a stand-and-deliver on-drive is punched down the ground past a diving Pattinson in his follow through and too well timed for mid-on to have a chance
brings out the reverse sweep, misses and gets taken on the pad...not quite sure that's needed right now
goes onto the back foot and works this out to deep square
swept again, well placed and it nearly reaches the boundary but deep square-leg is able to get the slide out
stretches forward and drives through cover to the sweeper
short outside off, Bell cuts and gets beaten by some extra bounce
on off stump, skids on and it's defended to the covers
angled across Stokes, who drives hard and misses
solidly defended by Stokes on off stump
good delivery, right length from Coulter-Nile and this nips away from around leg stump past the edge outside off - tough one for Stokes
drives clunkily down past the bowler

oh, nearly a chance here! Stokes gets sick of the lack of runs this over and tries to close the face on this to work it to leg, instead it's a leading edge that lobs only just over the head of Maxwell at point
pushed away to the off side
punched away to the off side
quickish from Maxwell, Stokes defends
tries to turn this to leg and it's another leading edge
tossed up a bit more now and Stokes tries to defend, gets a thick inside edge onto the pad and it lobs up safely to leg
goes the reverse sweep now and doesn't get this far past the keeper
turned away behind square leg now
banged in shorter by Coulter-Nile and Bell now gets a leading edge - a few of them in the last couple of overs - just lobs back in front of him on the pitch
yeah yeah no! That's the call from Bell as he nudges to off and nearly sells Stokes down the river - the no came quick enough for them to both get back safely though
opens the face and steers the late cut down to third man
good bowling from Coulter-Nile here, he pushes it across Stokes on a good length and the batsman plays and misses
waits on a late cut now and works a single behind point
what a good shot this is! Bell leans forward and lifts Coulter-Nile over mid-off, it bounces away for a boundary. Initially it was hard to tell how well he'd timed it - the answer was very.
probes outside off and Stokes leaves it alone
lovely ball as Johnson goes fullish and swings this away late - Stokes drives at it just outside off and doesn't really get the bat near it
goes the yorker again but it's just a touch short and Stokes keeps it out well

Johnson draws the edge from Stokes but this has fallen short of Marsh at first slip! And it's fallen quite a way short - perhaps Marsh is a touch too deep because you'd expect those to carry at the WACA
clipped away to Finch who is patrolling the deep midwicket boundary
Stokes drives outside off and places this nicely between point and cover and the outfield is super fast - he didn't time it that well but this has almost reached the boundary
a touch short outside off and Stokes waits on this for a late cut into the ground
Bell defends with a straight bat
dabs this away towards point
again Bell tries to steer this fine of point but again he's not quite got it fine enough

oh dear, Pattinson has misjudged one in the deep and it has brought Bell his half-century. Bell went inside out over cover and Pattinson was on the boundary there, but he's taken too many strides in and misjudged this - the ball goes over his head and bounces for four! Had he stayed back that may have been a reasonably straightforward catch. A let-off for Bell.
pushed away defensively
left alone outside off and this wasn't far away from the top of off
Stokes goes for the pull off a bouncer here and it runs along the ground to deep square leg

oh, it's another life for Bell! This time Marsh at first slip has dropped it! Not an easy chance as Bell opens the face and tries to glide this wide of slip, it's within reach of Marsh who thrusts the hands up to his right and can't hold on, just parries the ball away towards third man
cut away for two into the deep
clipped away well through square leg and Stokes picks up a boundary as Johnson goes too far towards leg

another drop! And again it was a really difficult one for Marsh at first slip. Stokes gets a genuine edge and this one flies to where second slip would have been - if there was one. Marsh dives to his left and gets the hand to this but it doesn't stick.
fullish and wide of off, Stokes flashes hard and gets a thickish edge away to third man
131kph from Christian on the stumps and Bell defends
Christian gets the line wrong now, down leg side for a wide
Bell drives hard again over the infield and this one is into safe territory, between cover and mid-off and Coulter-Nile gets around to cut off the boundary

Bell is gone! Oh, he'll be so frustrated at himself here. It was a bad ball down leg and Bell goes for the glance but fine leg is up in the circle and takes the catch easily! That didn't look like a plan from the Australians, just a fortuitous piece of, well, fortune.
driven away towards point
Ballance gets himself off the mark with a drive through cover point
driven away to cover and can't beat the field
on the back foot now and cut forward of point
beaten outside off now as Stokes tries to cut late - he's cut too late to get any bat on the ball
nudged away to off
Stokes uses the feet and drives back to Maxwell
crunched through extra cover for a couple more
short and wide, beats Ballance and is also too wide for the umpire's liking - he's called it wide
just waits on this one and dabs it towards off, they take off for a quick single and Maxwell running in from point fumbles
pushed right across Stokes, who leaves it alone
pushed away defensively to the off side
Stokes slashes hard outside off and this again is too wide from Christian - umpire Dharmasena is not having that
Stokes steers this through the vacant slip region and it's collected at third man
pushed down towards mid-on and can't beat the field
again Christian just angles it across the left-hander, this time it very nearly tickles the edge on the way through to Wade
Stokes goes for the big swing now and misses
on the back foot Stokes punches down the ground to mid-off
pushed away to mid-on and they can't find a run
driven hard back to the bowler
tries the late cut but it's too full and Ballance can't find the gap
wide of off and Ballance drives hard to deep cover
Ballance goes aerial now over midwicket and this just stops dead in the turf in the outfield like a well executed chip onto the green
worked away through midwicket along the ground now
Christian again goes well across the left-hander, who slashes hard and his edge flies down on the bounce to third man
goes uppishly over the cordon again and bounces down to third man
Stokes walks across his stumps now and tries to work it behind short fine leg - can't beat him though
worked away for a single to end the over
pushed away to cover and can't beat the field
finally England go after Maxwell and rightly so, as he dropped too short here and was pulled confidently through midwicket
advances and drives to mid-off
Ballance waits on this and plays late - cutting through point
drives along the ground to long-off
93kph from Maxwell on the stumps, it's defended
cuts hard and finds the man at point
Stokes has got this pull out of the middle of the bat but it's also smashed into the middle of Shaun Marsh's hand at midwicket - on the bounce
defended away to the off side
good ball beats the bat! Faulkner brought the length back just enough but Stokes was committed to trying a drive - the ball also nips away a tiny bit and beats the edge
steered away to third man now
Ballance waits on this and turns a single towards midwicket
cuts hard and this goes into the turf and back past Wade
angled on to the pads now and it's worked fine
93kph from Maxwell so he's bowling pretty quick at times, it's nudged away to leg for a single
quick and flat again, this one is down leg though
tossed up a touch more and the cut can't beat the infield

Stokes has had enough, he has advanced to Maxwell and lifted this over long-on for a really well-struck six that goes many rows back into the crowd, he just hit through the line of the ball and played it well enough to clear the boundary. And bring up his fifty
defended away safely

punched away to cover and they take a quick single - and it's a run-out chance that goes begging! Coulter-Nile is not deep at cover and pounces, throws at the bowler's end and misses. But Ballance had given up on that - he was gone
pushed away to the off side
beaten outside off now
a hint of outswing and this also beats the bat of Stokes
drives towards short cover and this time there's no thought of a run
drives down to the mid-off in the circle
pushed to the off side
gives himself some room towards leg stump so he can drive square through point
this drive firmly but straight at cover
picks out the fielder again, the same man at cover
almost a leg-side stumping, fired down the leg side but it was just too wide for Wade to get back in time
pushed to the off side
driven out to the deep sweeper...another tight over from Maxwell
plays and misses as he tries to drive on the up through the covers

has this carried? Marsh, the catcher, isn't sure so it's not quite like the previous match. Was flicked firmly by Stokes and Marsh dived forward. As usual, will be tough to see on TV replays. Marsh immediately said he wasn't sure. Not much excitement from the fielders. And it's not out
chopped down to third man
aims to guide this to third man, gets it finer than he wanted past the diving Wade but he benefits with a boundary
full outside off, driven on the up behind square on the off side
drives and misses, full outside off but Ballance was quite into the ball with his footwork
cracking shot, superb piece of timing through midwicket...Johnson homing in on leg stump but Stokes whipped it away strongly
slower ball on off stump, 129kph, defended to cover
dropped a little shorter outside off, driven square off the back foot through point out to the sweeper
good short ball, on off stump, and it climbs past Ballance's outside edge as he fends at it...close to the gloves
turns this delivery, which is short of a length, into the leg side
pulls a short ball over midwicket, more top edge than middle but it falls safely
comes at the bowler and bunts this straight down the pitch, Pattinson gets his right hand to it
shuffles across to off stump and flicks this in front of square on the leg side
short over middle and off, Ballance sways out of the line
that will boost Pattinson. Banged in a short, Ballance goes for the pull and gets a meaty top edge which goes now further than cover where Smith negotiates the sun to hold the catch
short again, this time Stokes connects cleanly with his pull through midwicket
full at off stump and worked down the ground to long-on
short on leg stump, rolls his wrists on the pull down to long leg
gets a short ball first up, over off stump, Morgan sways out of the way
good delivery, fuller outside off stump and Morgan nearly feels for it before pulling his bat away at the last second
ooh, close! Full and he drives in the air just wide of point to get off the mark
full on off stump, defended towards mid-on
lovely shot, pitched up on off stump and Stokes pings a punchy off-drive straight of a diving mid-off. Superb timing
starts full on middle and off, punched sweetly down to long-on and that's 200 for England
strong bottom hand from Stokes as he takes this from outside off down to long-on
down the pitch then up and over he off side, a length ball outside off  and Morgan drives to deep cover
good comeback from Faulkner, nips this away off the seam as Morgan tries to open the face
fuller and pushed down the ground

big wicket! Stokes tries to lap-sweep a slower ball but can only get a top edge that loops behind him and Matthew Wade trots around for the catch. They check the no-ball, it's very tight but is just okay. Bit close for comfort.
full outside off, Bopara comes forward and defends on the walk
full outside off, defended square to point
tries to get forward and drives without much timing to cover
touch shorter, played into the off side...four dot balls to build the pressure
nudged into the leg side to get off the mark
nearly an edge as Morgan tries to run this into the off side, the ball slides across him over the top edge. Was a noise as the ball went past the bat
on off stump, defended to the covers
opens the face into the off sid
short of a length, dropped square into the off side
tucked off his hip behind square
fuller this time, driven very firmly and it's the air for a while but falls short of cover
opens the face towards short third man...just four singles off the over. Australia clawing back well.
beaten again as he tries to run down to third man...Coulter-Nile has come back well after his first two overs were expensive
back of a length, played square to point
he's middled that okay...pushed up fuller outside off, allows Morgan to drive and he slots it wide of mid-off
straighter this time, worked off the stumps towards mid-on who can't stop a sharp single
tries to manufacture something now, moves outside leg to open up the off stump but can't make contact and is almost bowled
and now he's gone! England losing their way. A length delivery, Bopara tries to pull but can't get it over mid-on where Doherty runs backwards, keeps his eyes on the ball and holds a good catch
short of a length on off stump, played into the covers
on leg stump, worked behind square
another short ball, but this time Morgan puts it away, angled towards leg stump and he helps it over short fine leg
that's better, adjusts his line to outside off and there's some extra bounce to take it through to the keeper
fuller outside off, think it was a slower one, Morgan drives down to long-off
worked towards mid-on who hits the stumps direct but Buttler is safe
bouncer from Coulter-Nile and that could nearly have been called a wide, but he gets away with it
worked away off the pads
tickled away to fine leg for a single
soft hands from Morgan as he edges this away safely wide of slip and third man does well to get across and cut this off
defended back towards Coulter-Nile
driven away to mid-off and can't beat the field
worked away off the pads through square leg and they've done well to turn this into two
short ball from Faulkner and a delayed wide call by the umpire
this time they take the quick single to mid-on and Finch's throw misses at the non-striker's end - Buttler was probably quick enough to have been home anyway
this time they take the quick single to mid-on and Finch's throw misses at the non-striker's end - Buttler was probably quick enough to have been home anyway
there's the slower ball out of the back of the hand, and Morgan drives hard into the ground and back to Faulkner
again slower from Faulkner, again picked by Morgan
defended away safely again
soft hands as Buttler nudges to off but can't justify a single
banged in at the hips and Buttler pulls it around the corner for a couple of runs
on the pads and again Buttler works it away behind square
down leg side now and that will be called a wide - Morgan went the big hook but couldn't connect
now it's the slower bouncer and Morgan goes the hook before picking the speed, then adjusts and swivels it finer
good placement from Buttler now as he drives wide of mid-off and this one runs away for four, all the way along the ground
turned away off the hips for another run to fine leg

Buttler tries to turn this one down fine leg but gets nothing on it - this is called a wide by Dharmasena and that seems a tough call, Buttler walked across his stumps and this was barely down leg at all
pushed back down into the ground by Buttler
again Buttler walks across his stumps and this time turns it behind square
Morgan flicks it away through square leg and immediately takes off for the single
bouncer from Coulter-Nile and Buttler shapes to hook then backs out - it's called a wide
short again and this time Buttler hooks along the ground through square leg
aims at the hips of Morgan, who just nudges a single to leg
Buttler is on the back foot as this is again short of a length, he pushes a single behind point
Johnson at 143kph beats Buttler outside off
well struck by Buttler as Johnson gives him a touch of width at a driveable length and Buttler obliges by punching this soundly through the gap at cover
swivels a pull through square leg now and good running once again makes this into two
even better now from Buttler, again he goes the pull but this is timed and placed better, fizzes along the ground and away to the boundary behind square leg
pulls again and this one is collected in the deep
left alone outside off, which is a touch surprising at this stage of the match
muscular pull from Buttler as he gets one that is barely too short, but he's forced it through midwicket where Finch can't quite get a hand on it
Buttler backs off now and Coulter-Nile follows him, well bowled
the Buttler serves up something special here! He's lifted Coulter-Nile over long-on, just a strong, well-timed shot that clears the boundary and goes a long way back. Hefty six, that
flicked away towards fine leg for a single
tries for the yorker but it turns into a low full toss, it's clipped through square leg
full and wide of off, well bowled by Coulter-Nile as this was within the painted lines that guide the umpires on wides - but only just. Buttler reached with feet planted and couldn't get bat on ball
good ball as Johnson goes full and straight - and slow - Morgan can only bunt it away to off for a single
129kph as Johnson drops short, Buttler goes the pull and his under-edge nearly clips the off stump on the way through to Wade - done for a lack of pace there
Buttler clears the boundary again, and this one is square of the wicket - he's opened up his stance a little to clobber this up and over square leg - very, very well struck
miscues this one as he crunches it away to midwicket
now it's Morgan who tries to lift Johnson over square leg for six - but this one doesn't quite make it, it bounces to Coulter-Nile in the deep
Buttler swats a pull to Marsh at midwicket, his throw misses at the non-striker's end
slower one down leg and Faulkner is lucky Buttler manages only to swivel a single to fine leg
another six, and this is starting to get away from Australia - Morgan went the slog off Faulkner and it turns into a top edge that flies away with the wind and over the head of fine leg
Morgan is gone, he has flicked a low full toss from Faulkner to midwicket where Christian takes a pretty straightforward catch.
Bresnan is the new batsman and he drives to mid-on
Bresnan picks up a bouncer and hooks away to the deep midwicket
Buttler picks up two runs with a soft-handed nudge through square leg and that's his half-century, he's consistently offered something for England with the bat in this series
good slower one from Pattinson at 113kph and it's surprised Bresnan by bouncing a little more than he anticipated - off the gloves for a single to fine leg
Buttler picks correctly here as he walks across and laps Pattinson's slower ball over the head of Matthew Wade. Easy runs if he gets something on it, and he gets plenty on it
four more as Buttler just flashes hard outside off and slices it uppishly between third man and point
this is super stuff from Jos Buttler. Super stuff. He's now gone down the ground with a strong smash in the air straight back over the head of Pattinson and this flies 20 rows back into the crowd
again Buttler tries to walk across and lap Pattinson over Wade but this time he doesn't make contact
Pattinson goes well wide of off and Buttler slaps this in the air down the ground for a single
Faulkner has the last over and he aims at the body, gives Buttler no room, and the batsman can't get it away
low full toss now and Buttler swings but finds mid-on - they turn down the single so Buttler can keep the strike
and that's why Buttler wanted the strike! Faulkner goes low on the pads and Buttler just picks this up off the legs and this flies over square leg and is put down by a spectator on the hill
Buttler's entertaining innings comes to an end, he's swung hard outside off and this slices off the top edge and flies away towards third man where Johnson comes in and takes the catch
another catch at third man! Would you believe it? Bresnan has sliced this one off the edge and Johnson makes good ground to his left to take the catch
no hat-trick for Faulkner and Broad has also managed to force a boundary through cover, well struck and that takes the total to 8 for 316

inn2.comm: short of a length, going across Marsh outside off, left alone
takes the thigh pad into the leg side
back of a length on off stump, defended towards mid-off (who needs to be ready for a catch with Finch on strike)
well, that was in the air but over cover rather than mid-off...wasn't a half volley, he just strode into the ball and lifted it on the up over the off-side ring
left alone outside off
well bowled, nips back off a length and beats Finch taking the top of the pad through to Buttler
nicely turned away off the pads through square leg
wrong line again, on the pads, and this time it's clipped away with the timing to reach the boundary...poor start from Broad
gets onto off stump, defended towards point
full and very wide, Marsh reaches for it and drives between the two men in the point area
that's more like it, some effort as he hits a good length and it nips past the outside edge
that's lovely placement from Marsh as he guides this delivery, with complete control, wide of second slip and fine of third man
that's a floaty wide delivery and Finch pounces on it with a strong cover drive...Australia up and running
and again, this is a better shot as he stands tall and drives strongly square of the wicket through point
drags the length back, that's better, and it shapes back into Finch as he shoulders arms
back of a length, runs off the thick outer part of the bat behind point
too full on the pads, doesn't quite adjust to the left hander, flicked down to long leg
gets away with some width this time as Finch cuts straight to Morgan at point
squared up a touch by a delivery on off stump, takes a thick outside edge to third man
full at off stump, driven very sweetly but straight to mid-off...came into the stroke nicely rather than hanging back which is when it goes in the air
big appeal for lbw, a full delivery which Finch plays across, but it was always heading towards the leg side. Cook, who is back on the field, quickly forgets a review
blimey, that's a powerful stroke...hint of width from Broad and Finch rifled it behind point with a lovely cut shot
full and straighter, Finch drives and is a little stuck in the crease this time, the ball takes a thick inside edge to long leg
on off stump, defended to the leg side
goes for the pull, gets just enough bat on it to evade midwicket
better length outside off, not too full, left alone
oh dear, now mid-on has let one through his legs. Tredwell the culprit. It was a well-struck on-drive, powerful from Finch, and it bobbled a bit but should have been stopped
good delivery, finds that length that leaves the batsman in two minds...left alone by Finch
full at off stump and driven firmly back at the bowler...his run-up then did not look smooth at all. He delivered from miles behind the crease. That's not good
full again and he steals a single to mid-on who is hanging quite deep
outside off, left alone
now he gets too full, although to be fair it's a wonderful cover drive from Finch. Everything was perfect as he just leant into the shot and placed it between cover and mid-off
pulls the length back and it's defended to cover
now he escapes a short and wide delivery which is cut within the stopping range of Morgan at point
helps a short ball into midwicket off the back foot
better ball, full on off stump, but excellent batting as Marsh drops it into the off side and is quickly called through
full at off stump, defended to mid-off
cut into the ground and it bounces to point
on middle and off, played carefully straight down the ground
good delivery, nips away off the seam and beats Marsh's outside edge

top catch! Marsh trying to guide this delivery down to third man, was a little close to him and the thick outside edge is grabbed by Bell diving high to his left at second slip. A good start from Bresnan is rewarded
on leg stump, glanced away down to long leg so he's off the mark straight away
short of a length at the body, Wade gets inside the line and tucks it down to long leg
short of a length outside off, climbs nicely through to Buttler as Finch lets it go
short of a length, on the back foot and defended to the covers
a touch fuller and wider, Finch opts to leave it alone although I'm sure he was tempted to throw the kitchen sink at it
back-cuts down to third man
gets behind the line and defends to the on side...a better over from Broad
nips back into Finch off the seam, this moved off quite a full length and beats the inside edge into the pads
flicked in the air in front of square
back of a length outside off stump, defended to backward point
punched square of the wicket to bring point into action again
a fraction fuller this time, he opens the face and runs it backward of point but also wide enough of third man for a second
short of a length at off stump, defended into the covers. Tight from Bresnan.
nice delivery, Buttler takes it above his head even though it pitched fairly full
another one past off stump, this time just at waist-height to the keeper
gets on his toes and punches this shortish delivery off the back foot to mid-off
finds the gap this time, just enough room for him to free his arms into a back-foot drive which beats a diving backward point
fuller this time, outside off, Finch hanging back a little but defends easily enough to cover
left alone outside off
on off stump, defended to backward point
a fuller delivery, Wade walks into his defensive push to cover
goes for the hook, there's an appeal for a catch by the keeper but it's a quick 'not out'. Was a bit late on the shot
defended with soft hands behind square, second slip has to run around to field
tight leave! This seamed back into Finch and ended up passing pretty close to off stump, although the bounce helps the batsmen here
nudged into the leg side
round the wicket, full on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
beaten as he tries to guide this to third man, the ball ran across him
worked to midwicket
full on middle, defended back towards Tredwell
this time he drives with more conviction down to long-on
a chance to the left hander, it's on off stump and defended on the back foot...tidy start from Tredwell
terrific shot! Finch breaks the shackles with a free swing of the arms to a full delivery, launching it straight down the ground over the sightscreen
from one extreme to the other, this is left alone outside off
short of a length, that's well run as it's defended towards mid-on who is giving away the single
on middle and leg, aims to work through midwicket but can't find the gap
tucked off the hip out to deep square
goes for the pull and gets beaten under the bottom edge by a lack of bounce
full on off stump, opens the face and placed into the covers
fraction shorter, played off the back foot and driven into the pitch
goes back again and opens the face towards short third man
nice footwork, skips down the pitch and whips it through midwicket to the left of long-on
flicked to midwicket
works the gap this time, takes it from off stump square on the leg side
short of a length, pulled through square leg
short again and pulled firmly to deep square leg
fuller on middle and off, Wade is across his crease and defends to the leg side
back of a length on off stump, defended to mid-off
chopped in the ground and it bobbles back towards the slips, was aiming to guide to third man but was cramped for room
handsome drive, on the up, but it picks out cover
Finch defends Tredwell back down the pitch
Finch uses the feet and tries to go over the top but this just chips out on the bounce to the sweeper at midwicket
Wade goes across his stumps and defends to leg
more use of the feet and Wade pushes out to cover
Wade drives down the ground for a single to long-off
Finch backs off the stumps and crunches through cover for a quick single
Finch waits on this and steers a late cut to third man and that brings up his half-century from 54 balls
tight line from Bresnan but Wade manages to punch off the back foot behind point and that's super running to turn that into two
on the pads now and Wade clips a run away through square leg
Finch defends to off from the back foot
slower delivery at 107kph and Finch watchfully defends it
Finch goes down the ground and that's high, high, high - if he'd played that in the BBL at Etihad Stadium it might have hit the roof - and he has got enough on it to clear the boundary
Tredwell sneaks in with his economical action and Wade pushes to off
uses the feet now and drives a single down the ground to long-on
around the wicket still to Finch, who clips it away to midwicket
Wade dances down the pitch and this skews off the thickish edge away to backward point
goes back into his crease now and cuts but can't beat backward point
Wade gets this one down along the ground past the bowler but long-on manages to cut it off
Wade tries the big swipe through leg but mistimes it
bad ball down leg and Wade does enough to get bat on that and tickle a fine boundary past the wicketkeeper
nudged away to third man for a single
straight bat from Finch as he defends back to Bopara
punchy drive down the ground from Finch and the man is at long-on to cut it off
Wade again mistimes it, he just can't quite get going now, and this clunks into the ground in front of him
Finch advances to Tredwell and drives a single down to long-on
much the same again now as Wade nudges a single down to long-off
Finch tries to create something now by backing away but Tredwell followed him, now he crunches to cover and can't find the gap

this time Finch backs off a touch and instead of going through off he lifts it high and long over long-on, that was six from the moment it left the bat. It's landed on the roof of one of the stands - so we'll have a delay as they find a new ball
well, Finch is still seeing it pretty well! He's clubbed Tredwell over long-on for six more, clean hitting this
Finch on the back foot punches to the bowler
defended back towards the bowler
again defended away to off
Wade tries to steer a single to point but Finch sends him back
oh dear, Wade has tried to force the pace now with a drive over long-off but all he's managed to do was find Cook in the ring
driven down to mid-on
straight bat from Bailey as he defends
fullish on the stumps and driven to mid-off
half-volley now but Finch can't get his drive past the man at mid-off
well, one run becomes two here as Finch pushes a quick single to mid-off but the throw to the non-striker's end results in an overthrow
punched back past Stokes for a single
Bailey pushes away to cover and can't get off the mark yet
fullish again from Stokes and Bailey's drive fails to beat mid-off
Finch nudges away to off but can't find a run
Finch waits on this one and steers a late cut away to third man
fullish from Bopara and Bailey gets off the mark with a drive just wide of cover
defended away towards cover
Finch again drives just wide of cover and picks up a single this time
on the pads now and Bailey just places this nicely through square leg and hares back for two
punchy drive from Finch into the ground but can't beat cover

Finch takes off for a couple of runs here - and doesn't get any. Off his body and he wants a quick leg bye but Stokes is quickly on to it, sends him back with a throw that hits the stumps. Then Finch wants an overthrow on the ricochet, but gets sent back by Bailey. A lot of work for no runs
shortish and steered uppishly towards third man on the bounce
Bailey plays back and gets struck on the pad, only the hint of an lbw shout from Stokes. It was probably a touch high, but was certainly accurate
bouncer now and Bailey goes the hook and then sort of drags the bat away
bouncer again and this one will be called a wide, it was down leg as well as too high
Bailey plays back and just nudges a single through midwicket
Bailey crunches the ball down into the ground and takes off for a single down to third man
another run to third man, Finch and Bailey seem happy to turn the strike over with singles where possible
that's some muscle from Bailey, gets a fullish ball on the stumps from Bopara and clears the front leg to thump that down the ground past the bowler for four
pushed back towards the bowler and a slight fumble from Bopara allows them to get through for a single
another dab to third man from Finch
pushed away to point on the bounce
driven down to mid-on
Stokes goes fullish and Finch drives straight back past the bowler for a single
now it's Bailey using the single-to-third-man option, just steering it off the face of the bat
Finch pushes away to the off side for no run
Stokes strays on to the pads but it only costs a single as Finch flicks it to fine leg

down leg side and this flicks something on the way through to Buttler. It sounded thuddy as if it was pad, and the caught-behind appeal is turned down. England want a review. Well, this is very interesting. The front-on view didn't seem to support the review but Hot Spot has shown something. A clear mark on Hot Spot from the side on camera and this is out! What a good review - the sound didn't seem like bat, but Hot Spot said it was off the face of the bat before the pad. After the umpires also double-check that the ball has carried, Bailey has been given out!
well, the loss of a partner hasn't worried Aaron Finch at all, he has just driven this magnificently through extra cover. Such great placement there, and this is all the way along the ground for four
waits on this now and cuts away towards third man
Steve Smith now in his first ODI for more than a year, leaves his first ball alone outside off
gets off the mark now with an edge sort of nudge off bat and leg behind square
a touch of inswing now from Jordan, Finch punches it into the turf and back to Jordan
on the back foot now Finch nudges a single through wide mid-on and keeps the strike
Stokes keeps up with the fullish length and Finch's drive can't beat mid-on
shorter now and Finch just works a single to square leg
Smith now picks up a single by driving the fullish Stokes length wide of mid-on
nudged away for another single to midwicket
good running as this is pushed away to cover and a quick single is completed
shorter and down leg - Finch can't get bat on ball and that's a wide
Finch enters the 90s now with a push and quick single to leg
worked away through leg side now
very quick stuff from Smith to hurry through for a single here as Finch nudges to the off side - Morgan was sharp off the mark but Smith was fast enough to get through for the one
defended away to the off side
and slip is in play in the 29th over of the chase! But it hasn't carried! Smith drives really hard outside off and this edge just dies a bit on Cook and bounces short of him.
Smith goes the power pull but it turns into a bottom edge into his leg
Smith drives but can't beat short cover
driven down towards mid-on and Finch moves up to 94
Smith defends away to leg
clipped away through midwicket and Smith can only get a single
a bonus run for Australia now as Stokes strays down leg
uppishly driven through cover - that was heart-in-mouth stuff as this flew just wide of the man at short cover and away for a couple more
swivels this off the hips and down to fine leg
Smith clears the boundary now! He got a bit of a short one and just went after it, a pull that flew low and flat and only just out of the reach of the man at deep midwicket
driven firmly to cover who parries it for a single
worked down the ground, nearly off a leading edge
and there it is, tucks a brace into the leg side for his second hundred of the series. Superb innings
dug out to the off side
driven out to deep cover
wrong line, outside leg stump and that's gift as he tucks it away fine past short fine-leg
full and driven to mid-on
driven into the off side
dispatched! Poor ball, dragged half way down and Smith crunches his pull between midwicket and mid-on. Cook needs better than this from Broad
and that's what he needs! Broad pitches up outside off, just a hint of movement away to take Smith's outside edge. Well bowled, just rolled his fingers across the ball to create some cut
full on off stump, comes forward and drives to cover
well bowled, short of a length, 139kph, targetting Maxwell's body and he fends it to the off side
angled into the pads, tucked out to deep square leg
tight to off stump, he plays it very late with an open face down to third man
keeping it full, comes forward and opens the face to place it wide of cover
places it past cover again, out to the sweeper
very full, almost a yorker, Finch can't get it further than the cover fielder this time
close! Another yorker, this one tails into Finch who jabs down then sees that the ball is bobbling close to his stumps but in the end has it covered
short of a length at off stump, dropped down by his feet and that's an easy single with the fielders quite deep
pushed into the pads, flicked past a diving midwicket
short of a length, chopped into the ground and straight to point much to Finch's annoyance
pushed into the off side off the back foot
short ball, Maxwell pulls and it doesn't quite come out of the middle so dribbles over the outfield
he ramps this down to third man, carried quite a long way in the air but was never in danger of being caught
short of a length, whipped behind square on the leg side and they pick out Tredwell for a second
hint of movement into Maxwell from a full length, pushed to point
gets a long way across his stumps, England excited for a moment but not really close to a good shout as the ball deflects to square leg
nicely bowled, full on off stump, no room for Finch as he defends
tucked off the stumps to midwicket who is inside the ring but right on the edge
first attempt to try something more expansive, steps to leg and heaves a full delivery to mid-on...good comeback over from Jordan
good start, tight on off stump, can only defend back to the bowler
massive moment! Finch guides a short-of-a-length delivery towards third man where Broad runs around the rope and holds a well-judged catch
angled into the pads, doesn't make contact and it runs back to Bresnan
charges down the pitch and lofts this down the ground, one bounce to long-on
fuller delivery, inside edge into the pad and it drops into the off side for a sharp single
short delivery, quickly onto the pull and places it well enough behind square to come back for a second
driven in the air but fine of backward point down to third man
that's a brilliant piece of placement, as close as Maxwell gets to deft touch as he flicks this delivery off his hip and bisects deep square and long leg perfectly
ah, then he follows something brilliant with something a bit more ugly as he advances down the pitch and outside leg stump then misses a heave to leg
low full toss speared down the leg side but a clip of either bat or pad saves him from a wide call...it was the pad
worked off middle and leg down to long leg
nicely bowled, 136kph and it tails into Christian who can only push it back to Jordan
goes for the yorker, dug out down to long-on
pushed down the leg side, Bresnan furious with himself...extra run, extra ball
back of a length outside off, well placed as he drives behind point and third man can't cut off the second
angled into the body, a little fortunate that this isn't glanced either side of short fine-leg but instead picks out the man
oh, that's a superb shot...full at the stumps and it's flicked backward of square with something appraoching a sweep to vacant fine-leg area
tries to follow him with a bouncer, but it's too short and is called another wide
attempted slower-ball bouncer and it gives away another wide down the leg side as Maxwell misses his pull...priceless for Australia. Maxwell, though, was actually beaten by the change of pace
fuller and worked into midwicket
on off stump, 132kph, blocked back down the pitch
short delivery, Maxwell pulls and gets a healthy top edge down towards third man who does well to keep them to a single
short of a length, takes the thigh pad behind square
short of a length, he tries to pull but picks out midwicket
excellent work on the boundary, a short ball was pulled away and was skipping over the outfield but Root, on as a sub, was very quick around the fine leg rope
uses his feet, which makes it a very full ball, and drives into the off side but can't quite beat the ring of fielders
stunning strike! Stand and deliver. It was a length ball which Christian sent way over long-on. A lovely shot, nothing like a slog.

strikes first ball! An excellent match continues for Stokes. It was a back-of-a-length cutter, gripped a little on the pitch, which Maxwell tried to swing with all his power through the leg side but only got a thin edge to Buttler
tight line on off stump and left alone
pushes away to off
good yorker, right line and Faulkner can only jam down and keep it out
solid in defence from Faulkner as he tries to get his eye in
wants a quick single to cover but sends Christian back in the end
driven hard through cover point but there's a sweeper out there.
banged in short of a length and Faulkner just sways out of the way
again Faulkner is happy to defend
opens the face on this and gets off the mark with a steer to third man
Christian does much the same now and guides a single to third man
defended away to the off side
worked away off the pads for a leg bye
punched away through cover
clipped uppishly through midwicket and that has nearly found the fielder, but not quite
shortish but Christian's pull is just for the single to deep square leg

another wicket and it's the big one! Faulkner will not be the hero today. The extra bounce has done for Faulkner as it did for Maxwell. Faulkner backs off a touch and tries to slash through off and a top edge sails safely through to Buttler
Johnson is keen to after it straight away, backs off a touch and crunches behind point
Broad at 135kph and Johnson just steers it away to point
too wide for Johnson, who just had the feet planted and didn't move, and good bowling as this is inside the wide guide line
bouncer now and Johnson ducks - this one hasn't been called a wide
powerful strike from Johnson now as he gets a low full toss outside off and crunches a drive through cover and through the gap for four
Johnson winds up for the pull but he can't quite time it
some inswing now and Christian just drives a single down to long-off
flicked uppishly off the pads to fine leg for a single
goes the bouncer now and Johnson ducks underneath it
bonus run now as Stokes skews this one down leg for a wide
bowled, middle stump! Johnson went the big swing and Stokes was accurate enough to hit. This is England's match now, it's hard to see any way out for Australia.
swivels a pull around and it's collected on the boundary
Christian backs off and has a swing but again it's not out of the middle, just a thickish inside edge
Coulter-Nile has to settle for a leg bye as he swings hard
Coulter-Nile swings hard now and misses
bouncer and Coulter-Nile isn't keen to play at it
Coulter-Nile tries to club this over midwicket and his leading edge flies uppishly to third man on the bounce
shortish and Christian's swing misses
at last Christian does get one out of the middle, he lifts a fuller delivery up and over wide midwicket and this bounces away for a boundary
Christian is gone now, yet another batsman in this match caught at third man. He's swung hard and a thickish edge is taken by a sliding Gary Ballance
steered away towards point
thickish edge away towards third man gets Pattinson off the mark
driven hard down the ground to mid-off
crunches this hard towards midwicket and they get through for a quick single
Pattinson pushes this away to cover for no run
beaten outside off now
wrong line for Jordan though as he strays down leg

is this it? Is this the win? No! Oh dear, Stokes has dropped a chance at deep midwicket! Coulter-Nile has launched this high out into the deep and it was a pretty straightforward chance that just slipped through the fingers of Stokes.
bangs it in short now for an above-the-head wide
Pattinson chips this over cover for another single
Jordan tries for the yorker, Coulter-Nile drives down the ground to long-on
this one beats the bat through to Buttler

another one has been skied and another one doesn't get taken in the deep! This one was a top edge that flew out towards deep square leg, the men from deep midwicket and deep fine leg converged but neither quite got there. Ballance from fine leg very nearly made it, but perhaps just misjduged it a touch
beaten outside off - or is it? Jams down on the ground to a wide one and Hot Spot shows a little tickle on the bat there but England didn't really appeal
thumps this out to deep midwicket in the air for a couple more
worked out towards leg
it's over! England have won! Pattinson skies a high top edge that flies over the head of the keeper, but Buttler is good enough to run back and take a well-judged catch
